{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":3,"result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Prompt Injection — OWASP MCP Top 10\n\nPrompt injection happens when adversarial text in a tool response manipulates the LLM into overriding its system prompt. Attackers commonly use imperative phrases that direct the model to discard its earlier directives, often followed by a malicious request.\n\n## Mitigations\n\nUse a guard that scans tool responses for instruction-shaped patterns. Don't blindly trust content from external sources (web pages, chat messages, emails) that flows through tool calls.\n\nSee CVE-2025-54136 (MCPoison) for a real-world example of this attack class against Cursor."}]}}
